### Types of Man–Environment Relationships — Summary Table

| Type of Interaction | Direction | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Resource extraction | Man ← Earth | Mining coal, pumping groundwater |
| Pollution | Man → Environment | SO₂ emissions, plastic waste in oceans |
| Land use change | Man modifies Earth | Forest to farmland, wetland to city |
| Climate feedback | Environment → Man | Floods, droughts, heatwaves due to warming |
| Ecosystem services | Environment → Man | Pollination, water filtration, carbon storage |
| Conservation | Man protects Environment | Protected areas, emission controls |
| Restoration | Man restores Environment | Reforestation, river cleaning |

